UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2050
1 A RESOLUTION urging United States Attorney General Pam Bondi to investigate
2 and prosecute individuals implicated in criminal activities related to the Jeffrey Epstein
3 files and recognizing the efforts of Kentucky's own Representative Thomas Massie in
4 securing their public release.
5 WHEREAS, Jeffrey Epstein was a convicted sex offender whose criminal activities
6 involved the sexual exploitation and trafficking of minors and whose network included
7 numerous high-profile individuals; and
8 WHEREAS, in 2025, Representative Thomas Massie introduced and led the
9 passage of H.R. 4405, the Epstein Files Transparency Act, which requires the Department
10 of Justice to release all unclassified records, documents, communications, and
11 investigative materials related to the investigation and prosecution of Jeffrey Epstein,
12 with limited exceptions for victim privacy; and
13 WHEREAS, in November 2025, the bill was enacted after passing the United States
14 House of Representatives with overwhelming approval, 427-1, and the Senate by
15 unanimous consent; and
16 WHEREAS, the enactment of the Epstein Files Transparency Act led to the release
17 of millions of pages of documents, images, and videos in late 2025 and early 2026; and
18 WHEREAS, these disclosures have revealed new details about Jeffrey Epstein's
19 network and potential associations with participants, as well as evidence that may
20 indicate additional criminal conduct, while also raising ongoing concerns about
21 incomplete releases, excessive redactions, and the need for full accountability; and
22 WHEREAS, the people of Kentucky, including the constituents of Representative
23 Thomas Massie, have a vested interest in ensuring federal law enforcement upholds the
24 rule of law, protects vulnerable individuals, pursues justice without fear or favor, and
25 builds on the transparency achieved through the Epstein Files Transparency Act; and
26 WHEREAS, the Kentucky House of Representatives commends Representative
27 Thomas Massie's persistent efforts to expose the Jeffrey Epstein files and believes that
Page 1 of 2
