UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2050
1 any credible evidence of criminal wrongdoing uncovered therein warrants thorough
2 investigation and appropriate prosecution;
3 NOW, THEREFORE,
4 Be it resolved by the House of Representatives of the General Assembly of the
5 Commonwealth of Kentucky:
6 Section 1. The House of Representatives urges United States Attorney General
7 Pam Bondi to direct the Department of Justice to conduct a comprehensive review of all
8 materials released pursuant to the Epstein Files Transparency Act, legislation
9 spearheaded by Kentucky's Representative Thomas Massie, and to pursue criminal
10 charges against any individual for whom there is sufficient evidence of violations of
11 federal law, including but not limited to sex trafficking, exploitation of minors,
12 conspiracy, or related offenses.
13 Section 2. The House of Representatives expresses appreciation for
14 Representative Thomas Massie's leadership in making the Jeffrey Epstein files public,
15 thereby advancing justice for victims and transparency for the American people.
16 Section 3. The Clerk of the House of Representatives is directed to transmit a
17 copy of this Resolution to the United States Attorney General, the President of the United
18 States, the Speaker of the United States House of Representatives, the Majority Leader of
19 the United States Senate, Representative Thomas Massie, and each member of the
20 Kentucky congressional delegation.
